=begin
  transmog_inventory.lic

  Scans a container for transmog items into a shared CSV across all alts.
  Run ;transmog_inventory help for full syntax and examples.

  Quick command reference:
    ;transmog_inventory [container]        scan container (merge mode, default: chest)
    ;transmog_inventory new [container]    wipe catalog, then scan fresh
    ;transmog_inventory search <query>     search catalog (boolean syntax supported)
    ;transmog_inventory remove <query>     remove matching entries from catalog
    ;transmog_inventory note <id> <text>   add or clear a note on an item
    ;transmog_inventory price <id> <amt>   set asking price (25k, 2m, free, clear)
    ;transmog_inventory setname <name>     set display name for the Transmog Exchange
    ;transmog_inventory upload             push catalog to Transmog Exchange web database
    ;transmog_inventory clearweb confirm   remove your entries from web database (keeps local CSV)
    ;transmog_inventory gui                browse and edit catalog in a point-and-click window
    ;transmog_inventory help               full command list with examples

       author: Mara
         game: Gemstone
         tags: transmog, inventory, locker, items
      contact: mara.lilly on Discord, @Lillymara on GitHub
    co-author: Claude (Anthropic) - claude.ai/code
      version: 2.1

  Changelog:
    2.1.0 (2026-06-27) - GUI browser (;transmog gui): searchable point-and-click
                         window with inline price/note editing and multi-select delete.
                         Bugfix: remove/rm now accepts a numeric item ID directly.
    2.0.0 (2026-06-21) - Shared CSV across alts with Character column; setname,
                         price, and char: search commands; upload uses display name.
    1.4.0 (2026-06-18) - Full boolean search syntax for search/remove/note.
    1.3.0 (2026-06-17) - "note" command with stable numeric item IDs.
    1.2.0 (2026-06-17) - "upload" command to Transmog Exchange (Supabase).
    1.1.1 (2026-05-31) - Bugfix: item return in ensure block; quantity persistence.
    1.1.0 (2026-05-31) - Merge mode, "new" fresh-scan, "remove" command.
    1.0.0 (2026-05-31) - Initial release.
=end

require 'csv'
require 'net/http'
require 'openssl'
require 'json'
require 'securerandom'

# Changelog:
# 2.1.0 (2026-06-27)
#   - New "gui" command (aliases: browse, ui): opens a GTK3 point-and-click browser.
#     Search box filters in real-time (same boolean syntax as the command line).
#     Price and Note columns are editable inline -- click a cell and type.
#     Multi-select rows and click Delete Selected to remove them from the catalog.
#     Widget creation runs via GLib::Idle.add on the GTK main thread to avoid the
#     "Not Responding" freeze that occurs when GTK is driven from a script thread.
#   - Bugfix: remove/rm now accepts a bare numeric item ID (e.g. ;transmog rm 154876914)
#     without needing to match it through the boolean text search, which excluded
#     the id field.
#
# 2.0.0 (2026-06-21)
#   - Single CSV per Lich install (transmog_inventory.csv) instead of one per
#     character. Scans from any alt are merged in; a "Character" column records
#     which alt owns each entry. Dedup key is now (full name + character).
#   - On first run, any old per-character CSVs in the transmog/ folder are
#     auto-imported into the new shared file.
#   - New "setname" command: choose your display name for the Transmog Exchange
#     (main character name, preferred alias, and/or Discord handle).
#     ;transmog_inventory setname Mara
#     ;transmog_inventory setname Mara discord:mara.lilly
#   - New "price" command: tag items with an asking price in silvers.
#     Supports shorthand (25k, 2m), "free" (0 silvers), and "clear".
#     Price = 0 / "free" appears as "Free" on the Transmog Exchange.
#     ;transmog_inventory price <id> 25000
#     ;transmog_inventory price <id> free
#     ;transmog_inventory price <id> clear
#   - Upload now uses player display name instead of character name, sends
#     discord_name, per-item price and character (alt). Display name is required
#     before uploading (set with setname first).
#   - Search/remove/note support new char:/c:/character: field prefix.
#   - CSV format updated: added Character and Price columns (backward-compatible
#     read of old per-character files).
#
# 1.4.0 (2026-06-18)
#   - Added full boolean search syntax to search, remove, and note commands.
#
# 1.3.0 (2026-06-17)
#   - Added "note" command with stable numeric item IDs.
#
# 1.2.0 (2026-06-17)
#   - Added "upload" command to push catalog to the Transmog Exchange (Supabase).
#
# 1.1.1 (2026-05-31)
#   - Bugfix: items returned in ensure block; quantity persisted to CSV.
#
# 1.1.0 (2026-05-31)
#   - Merge mode, "new" fresh-scan, "remove" command, shared catalog reader/writer.
#
# 1.0.0 (2026-05-31)
#   - Initial release.

